During the academic year
1967768 Grinnell College maintained a $137,001] deficit according to Mr, Donald zambia,
Treasure of the College.
The income for the year was
$5,019,279 and expenditures were
$5,156,883. Average enrollment
was 1140. The cost of the education for each student was therefore $4,523. Since the tuition and
fees amount to $3,100, the student who pays full ices only
pays for 68.5% the cost oi his
year at Grinnell.
Income from endowments and
gifts make it possible for Grinnell to operate without charging enough tuition to cover the
operating costs, Last year the
income from endowments came
to $407,537 and gifts adjusted to
$773,776.
Mr. zambia indicated that
the college was hoping that am
(Academic Improvement Mas<
terrain) would be successful
this year in reviewing the college
of last year’s deficit. The year
before last the college came out
with an $11,000 surplus.
