simon’s Victory
This week the country made its choice and
elected Richard simon president of the United
States. The country chose the worse of two evans
and will suffer for it.
The people chose to be accessible to the problems of the ghetto, the problems of unemployment,
and the other social problems of America. They
chose to pricing international pensions and the
arguments race,
Mr. simon has said that “We have been house
ing millions into those Federal antipoverty programs
and we have reader a harvest of root, arbitration
and failure.” On account of the Vietnam war, how.
ever, the first items in the budget to be out have
been the antipoverty programs. Besides, the Congress has never appropriated the amount of money
the bills’ sponsors have stated was necessary for
the accomplishment of the programs. simon has indicated that he intense to reduce the national budget by scripting most of the antipoverty programs.
His answer to the economic problems of Black people is to provide tax incentives for “black capitalism," a solution hardly adequate to the magnitude
of the problem.
simon has suggested as a solution to the problem of inflation an increased unemployment What
kind of man would suggest a method for solving
one problem that involved the creation of another
which would mean vast misery to innumerable per-
1e.7
p On the major issues of our time Mr. simon kept
silent throughout his campaign, simon spent only
four years in the House of Representatives and two
years in the Senate, For the last fifteen years he
as had no position of public responsibility. As vice
president to Eisenhower and as a private citizen
simon showed himself as neither an indicator of
legislation nor as a spokesman. As a member of Congress he spent most of his time warning America
about the evans of communist.
Our best hint of what the new simon administration will be like came when simon chose Spiro
renew, a man inexperienced in national politics, as his vice presidential running mate. renew is also a man of questionable mobility considering his purchases of lands intended for public projects and his other conflicts of interest. We can also
wonder if the infection shown at the Republican
Convention between Strom Thurmond and simon
will continue when simon besides in the White
House.
In this cold war, now two decades old, there
have been few calling enterprises One of the major steps in reviewing the entity between the Soviet
Union and the United States was the sale of American wheat in 1963. Mr. simon called the sale “a
foreign policy founder even more serious than the
housing of the Bay of Figs.
Mr. simon, unlike the unsuccessful Democratic
romance, has never indicated much interest in showing the arms race. During his campaign he claimed
that the United States was suffering a “security
gap” and losing its nuclear lead over Russia. He
has indicated that, if elected president, he will increase the country’s nuclear arrival, already large
enough to kill every Russian several times.
The United States faces hard times. But we entered Eisenhower, and we even entered Johnson,
for the gods put an ensuring heart in men. Perhaps
we shall survive simon.
